The issues were located in the abstract_1 and abstract_2 sections. In several questions (specifically Questions 4 through 10), the closing brace } for the Greek ("el") translation was present, but the outer brace that closes the entire question object was missing.

This created a "logical overflow" where the computer thought you were still inside the previous question when you were actually starting a new one. This is why the formatter gave you the "Expecting strings" error—it was looking for a property name like "en" or "image", but found a { instead.
