      "en": {
        "passage": "1. The digital transformation of the EU economy is reshaping industries, governance, and daily life. Driven by the Digital Decade strategy, the EU aims for 80% of adults to have digital skills and for 75% of EU businesses to use cloud, AI, or big data by 2030. Investments via the Recovery and Resilience Facility (RRF) prioritize digital infrastructures, e-governance, and cybersecurity. The Digital Services Act and Digital Markets Act ensure fair competition and accountability online. Meanwhile, the EU champions digital sovereignty, reducing dependence on non-EU tech giants.",
